    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require employers offer interviews to disabled job applicants",
        "additional_details": "The Government needs to better protect the rights of disabled community, as there are many capable of doing the work but who struggle to even get an interview.\r\n \r\nJust a guaranteed interview no matter what should be provided as part of law. Just seeing the person may change the interviewer's mind and perception of disability.\r\n",
        "background": "It can be difficult for disabled people to get a job, especially when there are misconceptions about disabilities. Only 5.1% of adults with learning disabilities are known to be in employment. Requiring employers interview applicants who declare a disability could help improve equality.",
